snippet.textDisplay: I predict that Apple's transition to ARM will result in differentiation between PRO products and consumer products.  PRO products will continue to use x86 processors while consumer products will use ARM. It's the difference between rendering large audio/video projects and support for all of the plugins involved and a complete lack of support. Remember, the audio/video industry has a history of MAC support as a standard. If that standard no longer works, nobody is going to support Apple in that industry. Besides, all of the reasons that Apple became a major player in that industry have become null/void in the last 10 years anyhow. So what if Apple is going ARM? They might as well try something new and make the best of it. Because they have been dominated by their competition in the areas they used to dominate. If I owned a lot of stock in Apple, I'd be dumping that mess very soon. Rome is falling.
